                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P. W./1245</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-01">December 1,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Netherlands Minister informed me by telephone this morning that the
                    Government of the Netherlands East Indies had ordered a comprehensive
                    mobilization of its armed forces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">tanley</hi>] K. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ornbeck</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
